<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Luck" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Luck,</orth> 1) fortune, good or bad: <cit><quote>good or evil l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 14.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 14, 3</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>good l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.5.84" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 5, 84</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.61" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.221" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 221</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.41" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 3.3.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 3, 69</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.3.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 3, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.402" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 402</bibl>. <cit><quote>better l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 5.1.136" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 1, 136</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>ill l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.120" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 120</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.99" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 1, 99</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.99" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 1, 99</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.99" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 1, 99</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.51" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 1, 51</bibl>. <cit><quote>bad l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.41" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 1, 41</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>worse l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 2.2.59" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 2, 59</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>hard l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 5.2.158" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 2, 158</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>lean l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 3.2.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 2, 93</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) without an adj., good fortune: <cit><quote>if it be my l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.4.67" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 4, 67</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>if we have unearned l. now to scape the serpent's tongue,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.439" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 439</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>as if that l. bade him win all,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 5.5.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 5, 41</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of that natural l., he beats thee,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 2.3.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 3, 26</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>mock the l. of Caesar,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.289" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 289</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>was there ever man had such l.!</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 2.1.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 1, 1</bibl></cit> (Cloten is speaking of his adversary).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>